"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Erythrodermic psoriasis may be acute or chronic. It is characterized by generalized erythema and scaling from head to toe. Patients are at high risk for complications related to loss of adequate barrier protection such as infection (including sepsis) and electrolyte abnormalities secondary to fluid loss.",
